Based on the contractions and their intervals the app detects, it can inform you when you should go to hospital for delivery. Whether you have contractions every 10 minutes, every 5 minutes, etc., it is important to write them down.
3.- Contraction tracker: Here you will find a summary of everything you have registered so that you can keep track of all your contractions. You might have contractions without pain during your pregnancy (or even false contractions) you don't notice, but don't worry, the important ones will be those in the final stage of pregnancy.
3.- Tips and tricks: Here you will find some articles we have prepared to help you at this stage of pregnancy. Different types of labour pain symptoms, how to identify them, how to time contractions, stages of pregnancy, etc.

Main characteristics of the app contraction timer:
* Contraction tracker, contraction counter and tips: An all-in-one app to help you in the final stage of your pregnancy.
* No matter if you have uterine contractions or braxton hicks contractions, this pregnancy tracker app will be very helpful to count and monitor them. 
* This app is not a pregnancy calendar or pregnancy calculator. Its purpose is to help you count the kicks during all stages of labor.

Informative note: This contraction app is an informative app and it should not be considered as 100 % true under no circumstances, due to the fact that it is based on estimations and is no medical or scientific test.

title: Ovy Period Ovulation NFP
description:
Use Ovy to get pregnant or track your cycle naturally. Ovy combines an App and fertility thermometer to predict your menstrual cycle including the exact day of your ovulation, your fertile window and the beginning of your next period - applying proven science. Ovy is a class 1 medical product. 

Know when you’re most fertile and monitor your reproductive health through your iPhone. The self-learning algorithm is based on the highly recognized symptothermal method (NFP method) which is recommended by gynecologists to women globally.

--------------------------------

How it works: 
+ Set up your profile by completing the onboarding process. 
+ Take your temperature first thing every morning before you get out of bed.
+ Wait until you hear a signal or until the timer is up. 
+ Enter your temperature in the App to see your temperature curve. 
+ Tell Ovy how you feel by adding body signals such as period, PMS, discharge or mood swings. 
+ Add the first day of your period the day it starts. 

Why you should use Ovy:
+ Free of charge, no subscription model
+ Apply the well recognized and scientifically proven symptothermal method aka. as Natural Family Planning method. 
+ Know the exact day of ovulation, your fertile window and next period
+ Get pregnant or track your cycle naturally 
+ Apply a combined system of cycle app and fertility thermometer for accurate prediction 
+ Access to Ovy Care that helps you meet your fertility goals
+ Get a reminder for temperature measurement and data input 
+ Convenient and intuitive user experience 
+ Clean and simple design 
+ Classified as medical device 

Ovy hacks: 
+ Use Ovy’s fertility thermometer or any other device with two decimal places. 
+ Place your thermometer on top of your phone before you go to sleep. 
+ Check if your temperature curve appears normally. If not change the measuring site (oral or vaginal) but make sure you stick with one during a whole cycle. 
+ Make use of the 3 minute timer in case the shortened measurement time leads to unsteady curves
+ Set a reminder, so you won’t forget to add your daily data.
+ Complete your profile - try to remember your last period.
+ Add temperature interference to make predictions more accurate. 

More than a cycle app 
Ovy’s smart algorithm understands how your hormones influence your well-being during the four phases of your menstrual cycle. Ovy Care helps you to achieve optimal balance by providing meaningful content based on nutrition and fitness. Ovy helps you handle period cramps, increase your energy and get the glow. Just check out Ovy’s meal- and workout tipps.

title: EDCpro
description:
Expected date of confinement (EDC) calculator for doctors. 

1. Info to EDC; EDC will be determined by ovulation, the last menstrual period (LMP), CRL size, BPD size, the date of embryotransfer (as 2W2D), and the date of blastcyst transfer (as 2W5D). When you touch the selected EDC, the pregnancy calendar is displayed. The CRL/BPD data are based on the Japan Society of Ultrasonics in Medicine.

2. EDC to Info; At first, the EDC should be input. Then the pregnancy calendar is displayed. You can know the gestational week and day if you input the date you want to know. You can know the date if you input the gestational week and day.

3. Gestational week to Info; When you input the date and the gestational week which you want to investigate, then theEDC and the pregnancy calendar are displayed.

The EDC input is available from Jan 01, 1904 to Jan 01, 3000.

NOTE; The gestational month counting system in Japan is different from others.  Traditionally, the first 4 weeks (0W0D-3W6D) is counted as the 1st month in Japan, though zero month in other culture.
The Japanese counting system is used when you run in Japanese laguage system (Settings->General->International->Language). The western system is used when you run in English laguage system.

title: EDClite
description:
Expected date of confinement (EDC) or due date should be determined by your doctor.
The gestational weeks and days at 40W0D (280th day) is the EDC. Pregnancy lasts about 38W0D (266 days) since fertilization.  
Then, the beginning of the last menstrual period is the basis of calculation as 0W0D.
But, the early stage of embryo size measured by ultrasound or the date of embryo transfer or the blastcyst transfer is more accurate.

The delivery is classified as abortion (-21W6D), preterm delivery (22W0D-36W6D), term delivery (37W0D-41W6D), postterm delivery(42W0D-).
NOTE; The gestational month counting system in Japan is different from others.  Traditionally, the first 4 weeks (0W0D-3W6D) is counted as the 1st month in Japan, though zero month in other culture.
The Japanese counting system is used when you run in Japanese laguage system (Settings->General->International->Language). The western system is used when you run in English laguage system.

The EDC input is available from Jan 01, 1904 to Jan 01, 3000.

For EDC decision support tool for doctors,  EDCpro, is for sale in iTunes Store.

title: Start Smart for Your Baby by Louisiana: Pregnancy
description:
Use this app to: 
- Make a personalized action plan for your own healthy pregnancy

- See weekly ultrasound videos illustrating your baby’s development
- Find out when you hit important milestones
- Look up symptoms and issues
- Get daily tips and affirmations
- Find your health plan’s pregnancy program information
- Calculate your due date

Start Smart for Your Baby by Louisiana Healthcare Connections helps you connect to Louisiana Healthcare Connections staff and resources, create your pregnancy action plan, track your pregnancy milestones, look up your and symptoms and issues, so you can have a healthier pregnancy.

And there is more...The big day is coming! So many things are changing and there’s much to learn. For one, how can you best manage that “morning” sickness that seems to show up any time of day? When will your baby have a heartbeat? And what do your ultrasounds mean? 

Begin by using Start Smart for Your Baby to make a healthy pregnancy action plan. Just enter your due date and birth date, and Start Smart begins personalizing your pregnancy milestones. After answering questions about how you're doing, you’ll learn about health issues related to your own pregnancy. 

You can also use Start Smart to look up any symptoms you’re having, see weekly ultrasound videos of how your baby is growing, and track your weight gain. Can’t seem to remember to make that appointment or drink enough water each day? 

You can even set reminders so you won't forget the important things to do when you’re pregnant.

Along the way, make a list of things to talk about with your doctor. When you see something you want to talk about to your doctor, midwife, or nurse, you can add it to your Hot List to easily remember at your next appointment.

Start Smart is developed in conjunction with a board certified OB who has over 15 years' experience taking care of women and their babies. Other contributors include nurses, midwives and other medical experts.

Visit Louisiana Healthcare Connections to learn more about the resources and services they provide to help take care of you and your baby.

title: Next Level Mobile
description:
Because a file cabinet won’t fit in your pocket or purse, Next Level’s mobile app brings the power of the pro-life community’s most robust center management tool to your smartphone. Use the app in your center, take it on the go, or hand it to a client for intake wherever you meet her.

The Next Level app allows you to toggle between client and staff modes on a mobile device, so you can securely enter and update any client’s information while she’s still sitting knee-to- knee with you.

Plus, the Next Level app allows you to look up any donor’s information on the go, allowing you to make the most of divine appointments at a banquet, church parking lot or grocery store.

Designed by a team of professional healthcare software developers, Next Level closes the loop from receptionist to client, to advocate and nurse—all in real time.

Whether you’re meeting a client in your office, a church parking lot or on the go, your data is always secure and available at the tap of a finger.

Next Level also harnesses the power of big data, leveraging local and national trends to help you make the best decisions you can for the women you serve every day.

Incorporating the necessary HIPAA protections, Next Level is powered by Heartbeat International and crafted to manage pregnancy help efforts of all stripes—medical, resource, linear, mobile units, and more!

We start with your needs, envisioning the client you serve and wondering, “How can we make sure she never falls through the cracks?” And, we start with your center, “How can we save your center time, money and help you reach more women?”

While we’re pushing toward these two goals, we’ve got a larger mission in mind: “How can we make the life-affirming pregnancy help movement stronger?”

We believe it’s time to make a change. It’s time to take our movement—and your ministry’s client management—to the Next Level.

description:

You can perform simple searches by entering one or more letters in the search field. You can also search for names containing a certain pattern by using ? for an arbitrary letter and * for 0 or more arbitrary letters.
Example: ??U?? will find all names containing 5 letters, where the letter in the middle is a U, e.g. LAURA, PAULA and TRUDE. 
Example: M*AS will find all names starting with M and ending on AS, e.g. MATHIAS, MIKAS and MALIAS.

title: Health Is Vital
description:
This mobile app aims to provide basic, concise and clear information about HIV and AIDS to the general population in Northern Saskatchewan and beyond.

Through different sections the user can:
• Learn about HIV and AIDS basics.
• Review some of the common myths and facts related to HIV and AIDS through an interactive quiz.
• Review practical information about HIV prevention.
• Learn about simple steps that can be taken to make living with HIV easier including information about HIV treatment and HIV in pregnancy.
• Find information about HIV tests, getting tested for HIV and what the tests mean.
• Find links to useful and relevant resources  
• Find the location and contact information of testing sites in Saskatchewan, Canada through the GPS finder
The app was developed through Northern Healthy Communities Partnership (NHCP) as part of the Northern Saskatchewan HIV Awareness Initiative, the objectives of which are to encourage HIV testing and reduce stigma related to HIV and AIDS. NHCP is a group of organizations (public, private and non-for profit) who choose to work together to enhance the well-being of individuals, families and communities throughout Northern Saskatchewan.

title: Birthrisk
description:
ALL BODIES ARE GOOD BODIES, but not all bodies are equally likely to avoid a cesarean birth. Birthrisk will guide you through the results of millions of prior births.

Just select an age, a height and a body type and you will see the results achieved by women who have already given birth across the United States. The results may surprise you and you can easily share these results with others. No cost, no ads, no email, no personal info, no kidding.

Discover how age, height, body type, pregnancy weight gain, baby’s size and induction of labor affect the rate of cesarean birth. Results are based on data from millions of prior births obtained from the U.S. National Center for Health Statistics and updated to reflect the most recent data available.

Developed by an obstetrician with decades of experience and based on scientific evidence. As you discover the significant impact of physical characteristics on the rate of cesarean birth you will come to realize that asking your obstetrical care provider about their cesarean birth rate is meaningless unless you first know more about the women who are giving birth.

title: Baby is Coming

More than simply addressing the child-mother couple, he also speaks of the doubts of parents, gives advice to couples and tells stories. An app to further elevate the mood of pregnant women and "pregnant man".

title: OvuSense
description:
TAKE BACK CONTROL OF YOUR FERTILITY: OvuSense™ is an extremely accurate cycle monitoring system, unlike any other fertility tracker on the market. OvuSense can predict ovulation up to a day in advance, in real time, and detects the exact date of ovulation with clinically proven 99% accuracy. 
“I have been trying to conceive for five years. I signed up for the OvuSense App User Study when I saw they were looking for participants. Last month, I had my blood drawn to confirm ovulation, and the Doctor said I did not ovulate for the month of May. However, OvuSense said I did. My husband and I had sex all around the time OvuSense said I was in my ovulation window, and I woke up to...a positive pregnancy test. I’m so happy!” Courtney, 2016

OVUSENSE - THE MOST ACCURATE CYCLE MONITORING SYSTEM YOU CAN BUY: 
- Clinically proven in over 6,000 cycles of use: Clinical studies show that ovulation predictor kits (OPKs), and fertility tracker Apps can produce an incorrect result in at least one in every five cycles1, leaving you confused about when to try to get pregnant. 
- Real time 24 hour advance ovulation prediction: Unlike any product, OvuSense provides a day's advance notice of when you are going to ovulate in real time along with your 4 day ovulation window – with clinically proven 96% correct results.[2]
- 8 day fertile window: In addition, at the start of each cycle OvuSense provides a full 8 day fertile window - these features help you take back control of your planning for pregnancy.[2]
- 99% accurate patented technology: Protected by nine patents, OvuSense monitors your 'core temperature' while you sleep, giving a true indication of your Progesterone levels each cycle enabling the detection of the exact date of ovulation with 99% accuracy proven in clinical trials.[2] 
- Fully certified: OvuSense is a fully regulated medical device and complies with all the necessary certifications for the countries in which it is available – MDD CE mark in Europe, FDA 510(k) in USA, CMDCAS in Canada, TGA in Australia.

1: 	Arici A (1992). 48th AFS; ASRM (2012) Fertil Steril 98; Baird D (1995). Epidemiology 6; Irons DW (1994) Hum Rep 9; Kousta E (1999) Hum Rep 14; Lloyd R (1989) Am J Obstet Gynecol, 60; McGovern PG (2004) Fertil Steril 82; Rollason JCB (2014) IJWH 6; Robinson S (1992) Br J Obstet Gynaecol 99; Setton R (2016) Obstet Gynecol 2016 Jun 6; Vlaisavljević V (2007) Obstetrics and Gynecology. 1(20); Wise LA (2015) Fertil Steril Vol 104
2:	Coyne MD (2000) Am J Physiol Regul Integr Comp Physiol 279; Papaioannou S (2013) ASRM 69th An. Conf; Papaioannou S (2013) J Obstet Gynaecol 33; Papaioannou S (2012) ASRM 68th An. Conf; Papaioannou S (2012) ESHRE 28th An. Conf; Papaioannou S, Delkos D, Pardey J (2014) ESHRE 30th An. Conf.

THE OVUSENSE SYSTEM:
- OvuSense has two parts: a vaginal Sensor and an App. 
- You will require an OvuSense Sensor to measure your cycles. 
- The App charts and messages provide all the information you need to help you identify when you ovulate, giving you the best chances of conceiving.
- You can use the OvuSense App to share data with your doctor and family members.

TRUSTED BY WOMEN WHO HAVE BEEN LET DOWN BY OTHER PRODUCTS:

“I want to express how horrible ovulation predictor kits are for women with PCOS. I never had a positive or even close to one in all the months I used them. OvuSense confirmed ovulation on Wednesday Feb. 24th 2016 and I’m now pregnant! This OvuSense machine is amazing!! If you are considering buying…do it. So worth the money.” Eden Nicole, 2016

“I am pregnant after using OvuSense for two months. We were trying for 8+ years before that.” Kirsty, 2015

“OvuSense confirmed my exact ovulation date. I was amazed how late it was in my cycle! I had no idea how late I ovulated and I would have never guessed on my own. I knew that I might not ovulate every month, but at least I knew that I had this month. I never would have of have known that, or ‘when’ it was, if I didn't have OvuSense!” Jenny, 2015

title: ezPregnancy
description:
EzPregnancy - obstetric wheel is the essential app for midwives and obstetrician gynecologists.

EZPregnancy (pronounced "easy Pregnancy") lets you have your old cardboard wheel always with you on your smartphone or tablet, so that you never forget it between two gowns.

Interactive and completely customizable, you can choose to display only the information that you find relevant on the wheel, and then read the detailed timeline of your patient's pregnancy in the calendar.

Are included in the pregnancy monitoring:
- Pregnancy months and theoretical due date
- Consultations with the midwife or gynecologist
- Echographies
- Diabetes and Down syndrome screenings

With this pregnancy wheel, you can also compute the Body Mass Index (BMI) of your patient in order to prevent for excessive or insufficient weight gain during the pregnancy.

Some norms (Careful! these are based on French policies) are reminded to let you analyse blood tests for diabetes screening.

Designed with midwives for midwives, this app fits also gynecologists and pregnant ladies. In future developments, we will include information on pregnancy month by month, as well as fun facts such as chinese or western astrology.

Enjoy your pregnancy!

title: Color Breath
description:
I don’t think I need to say something if you read these reviews.

Pranayama aide with timing choice - Nice! (Jul 18, 2012) posted by Jonny0007
UPGRADED to 5 Stars! The developer added the guidance of sound-tones which was the only feature this app lacked (now you can close your eyes while you breath, if you wish). In my opinion, this breathing app is the BEST one out there IF: you want total control of the breath timing, you don't need instruction, and you don't want a lot of "bells and whistles" on your app. The app is simply designed and the visuals & audio foster relaxation nicely. Big thanks to the developers for the update!

Beautiful (Jun 29, 2012)  posted by Oinjjko
You could pay a lot for a breathing app and not get half of what this app gives you. Beautiful to view while you use breathing patterns you have total control over. Thank you for wonderful breathing app. Also the big timer in front of you is another beautiful feature. The timer can be displayed while doing breathing exercises or taken off the screen. The bubble audio is so relaxing, another wonderful feature. The developers got it right when they gave you total control of your breathing patterns, a lot of breathing apps don't give you this wonderful feature.

I feel grateful for these wonderful reviews. 


It has passed four years since the app was released. Version 5.0 is the first update in three years.

Now these new features are available.


Auto Stretch
You can find it in the timer setting view by pushing an clock shaped button which is located upper right.

Color Pick
Six pastel colors are set in the color buttons. But you can change the color as you like. Try long-press any color button to show a color picker.

Sound Only Mode
It was implemented in the old versions as Sleep Mode. You could breathe with sound navigation while you close your eyes, but needed to double-tap to add exhale time and single-tap to add inhale time. I loved to use the app with closed eyes, but it wasn’t comfortable. However you can use Auto stretch and Sound Only Mode at once now! Check off the box just below Auto Stretch setting pane.


I hope that you would love this version, too.


Thank you.

title: Rasedus
description:
Raseduse äpp võimaldab raseduskalendris jälgida raseduse kulgu, sisestada rasedust puudutavaid terviseandmeid, saada teavet rasedusaegsete uuringute ning sünnituseks ettevalmistuse kohta. Äpp sisaldab mitmeid praktilisi kalkulaatoreid. Raseduse äpp saadab sulle olulisi meeldetuletusi rasedusaegsete sündmuste ja toimingute kohta.
Äpp-iga on lihtne jälgida oma rasedust, saada infot rasedusaegsete muutuste, raseduse jälgimise ja eelseisva sünnituseks ettevalmistuse kohta ning üles märkida kõiki rasedusega seotud tähelepanekuid. See on hea võimalus asju meeles hoida , et neid vajadusel oma ämmaemandaga arutada.
Raseduse äpp sisaldab:
1.	Infot raseduse alguse, soovituste ja esimese ämmaemanda visiidi kohta.
2.	Infot raseduse kulu ja lapse kasvamise ning soovituste kohta kogu raseduse jooksul  nädalate lõikes.
3.	Infot rasedusaegsete uuringute ja analüüside kohta.
4.	Infot ja soovitusi enamlevinud rasedusaegsete kaebuste ja tervisemurede kohta.
5.	Infot rasedaid puudutava seadusandluse kohta
6.	Infot sünnituseks ettevalmistumiseks.
7.	Soovitusi mida kaasa võtta sünnitusmajja
8.	Infot ja soovitusi kuidas toimida erakorralistes olukordades
9.	Võimalust sisestada raseda päevikusse erinevaid terviseandmeid ja kasutada kalendrit rasedusaegsete sündmuste sisestamiseks.
10.	Salvestada fotosid ning jagada neid sotsiaalmeedias
11.	Võimalust sisestada ultrahelitulemusi ning sündinud lapse andmeid.
12.	Beebinimede raamatut.
13.	Soovitusi kodus vajaminevate beebitarvete kohta
14.	Raseduse äpp-is on kõik olulisemad rasedus ja sünnitusega seotud kalkulaatorid
•	Ovulatsiooni kalkulaator
•	Raseduse suuruse ja sünnitustähtaja kalkulaator
•	Sünnituspuhkuse alguse ja sünnituspuhkuse kestvuse kalkulaator

Äpp on kasutamiseks kõikidele rasedatele, aga ka neile, kes alles planeerivad rasestumist. Raseduse planeerimisel aitab äpp`i ovulatsioonikalkulaator välja arvestada kõige sobivama ajavahemiku viljastumiseks.

title: Weight Log Plus

title: Babyotchi
description:
BabyOtchi is a combined/portmanteau word for Baby + Watch. As a parent, most of your focus is on your baby's wellbeing, which for a baby is very related to how the baby is eating, sleeping and doing other routinely activities. The BabyOtchi iPhone app is designed to provide an easy and fast way to register, keep track and share your child's activities and needs. 

---Keep track of your baby's activities and needs
It is possible to register all kinds of activities concerning your child. All registrations will be available in a timeline and are also the basis for reports and recommendations on when it is time for the child to sleep or eat.

---Share routines with other caretakers of the child
Using iCloud, BabyOtchi offers features to share all information concerning your child with other caretakers of the child. When a caretaker registers an activity, all other caretakers will be notified about the event! For integrity reasons, only the creator of the child will be able to invite or remove caretakers.

---Reports
Several reports are available giving caretakers a thorough overview of your child's routines and needs. 

---Alarm functionality and units
You are able to turn on and off food or sleep alarms as well as choosing the  temperature or measurement units that you are familiar with.. 

Note: This is an iOS app and should not be seen as a replacement of caretakers' normal duties & responsibilities. We do not take any responsibility other than providing this app in its current shape and function.

BabyOthchi is an iPhone app and requires iOS 10.3 or higher.

title: PHC
description:
Mission
Championing the rights of women to receive full information on all of their options during an unplanned pregnancy and full understanding about the risks and complications of having an abortion.

title: Music for Pregnancy Exclusive
description:
Music for Pregnancy is a hand-picked collection of tracks that will help you increase a healthier and stress-free birth experience!

***Why download Music for Pregnancy?***

Classical music when played moderately has a calming effect rendering the heart to beat slower as well as the breathing to be deeper. This is because the music compels the brain to release endorphin which naturally relaxes the body.Thus, stress is reduced and mood is improved which are great for a baby’swell-being as well as for the caring parent. 

Babies start to hear at 6 months in the womb that is why mothers are encouraged to listen to classical music if at least just for its lasing effect for both baby and parent. Pregnancy is a special time but is riddled with stress and aiming for a calm disposition will likewise calm the baby inside. And because babies are likely to recognize the same music you played while he was still in the womb, the association will be comforting and provides baby with an extra sense of security. 

So it is definitely worth doing during your pregnancy and early infant years!

title: Folate and B12 Counter & Tracker for Healthy Diets
description:
Use this app to count, track, chart and control your folate (aka vitamin B9, folic acid) and vitamin B12 intake to avoid deficiency. Deficiency in women before or during pregnancy can cause brain and spinal cord birth defects in their children. Folate and vitamin B12 deficiency are also a cause of anemia. Additional app features include the at-a-glance descending order lists of folate and B12 content of >300 common foods in µg and %RDA (Adult Daily Recommended Dietary Allowance) /100g to help you plan folate- and vitamin B12-containing meals; and really useful hyperlinks to essential nutritional and healthy food information with ≈200 photos to support your weightloss, hearthealth or other diet. No internet connection, registration, personal details or additional payments required.
Folate  and vitamin B12 play key roles in DNA (genes) and red blood cell production. B12 deficiency damages the brain and nerves, and folate deficiency damages the skin and linings of the mouth and gut. B12 is not found in plantbased foods so vegans and vegetarians may become deficient if they don't take supplements. Alcoholics are prone to folate deficiency. 
Use the count and organiser tools to count, track and keep a daily bar chart record of your folate and vitamin B12 intake in µg and %RDA provided by 250 heart healthy foods, 55 popular "not heart healthy" foods, and foods you choose to add to the counter in the quantities you’ve eaten. 
The interface is easy, quick, and intuitive to navigate, colour-coded, searchable, and zoomable using the pinch screen function. Viewable in landscape and portrait.

title: Hampton Medical
description:
Hampton Medical is an innovative application for home monitoring of patients with hypertension and subsequently at risk of pre-eclampsia during pregnancy. Allowing patients to monitor and record blood pressure and urine results, Hampton helps distinguish women who actually need to attend the hospital for further assessment from those who can monitor their blood pressure at home with routine follow-up with their midwife or hospital.

Patient’s results are submitted and analysed with pre-set thresholds. If the readings are ‘safe’, the patient is reassured and encouraged to continue home monitoring. If their results are abnormal the app asks them to contact their midwife or hospital. 

The app is linked with a clinician portal that displays patient readings in real time.

title: iwater LITE | Hydration daily tracker and drink water reminder for your body balance
description:
"iwater" helps you drink water regularly. Calculate your daily water intake and get notifications!

Application features:

* Water requirement calculator
* Reminders
* Units (Metric and oz)
* Statistics
* Motivational awards


Health benefits of water?

Water is your body's principal chemical component and makes up about 60 percent of your body weight. Every system in your body depends on water. For example, water flushes toxins out of vital organs, carries nutrients to your cells, and provides a moist environment for ear, nose and throat tissues.

Lack of water can lead to dehydration, a condition that occurs when you don't have enough water in your body to carry out normal functions. Even mild dehydration can drain your energy and make you tired.

How much water do you need?

Every day you lose water through your breath, perspiration, urine and bowel movements. For your body to function properly, you must replenish its water supply by consuming beverages and foods that contain water.

So how much fluid does the average, healthy adult living in a temperate climate need? The Institute of Medicine determined that an adequate intake (AI) for men is roughly about 13 cups (3 liters) of total beverages a day. The AI for women is about 9 cups (2.2 liters) of total beverages a day.


Have fun!

It is brought to you by the Perinatal Depression e-Consortium (PDeC), led by the Parent-Infant Research Institute (PIRI) in partnership with Perinatal Anxiety and Depression Australia (PANDA), Jean Hailes Research Unit at Monash University, Jean Hailes for Women’s Health and Queensland University of Technology.

title: Prenatal Yoga Poses
description:
From your physical body to your emotional state, prenatal yoga is a key ingredient to a healthy, happy pregnancy.

Prenatal yoga sounds like a healthy practice to adopt during pregnancy -- and it is. But what specifically can yoga do to help you feel great and stay calm during the most important nine months of your life? Read on for seven important ways yoga can make a positive difference in your pregnancy.

Prenatal yoga classes are very popular, and when paired with a cardiovascular exercise (such as walking), yoga can be an ideal way for moms-to-be to stay in shape. Whether you're a newbie or a veteran, yoga can keep you limber, tone your muscles, and improve your balance and circulation during pregnancy – all with very little impact on your joints.

Yoga is also beneficial because you'll learn how to breathe deeply and consciously relax, which will be helpful as you face the physical demands of labor, birth, and new motherhood. Learning to breathe fully is actually one of the first things you'll learn in a yoga class. To use the breathing technique practiced in yoga, known as ujjayi, you take in air slowly through your nose, fill your lungs as you expand your belly, and exhale completely until your stomach compresses.

Can prenatal yoga be the first time I ever do yoga?
Yes! You don’t have to be a yogi before you conceive to jump on the prenatal yoga bandwagon. As long as your doctor has given you the green light to stay physically active during pregnancy, yoga is an ideal activity for all expectant moms: It’s gentle and designed for pregnancy, which means it helps prepare you for the mental aspects of childbirth (and beyond). But remember, it’s always a good idea to check with your doctor before starting any new exercise during pregnancy.

title: UmanMap
description:
UmanMap is an educational tool at once simple, complete and scientific that allows is to better know and understand human development. Allowing for a better comprehension of complete human function, UmanMap allows us to assess an individual’s progress in acquiring competencies and self-knowledge within the family and wider society; it sets out a new way of approaching this complex area through thought, understanding and the actions to be taken.

UmanMap is split into 3 developmental phases:
- Infancy
- Childhood
- Preadolescence, adolescence and young adult

It is a scientific document based on the human sciences and validated by child-development specialists, child psychologists and educators.

What purpose does it serve?

It proposes educational and pedagogical objectives in a precise, logical and objective manner. Thanks to UmanMap, everybody can immerse themselves in the world of child and adolescent development, allowing them to anticipate and prevent potential problems and stimulate further development constructively and appropriately.

Technically, how does it work?


UmanMap is built along a horizontal axis of time, defined in months and years, and a vertical construction around the 5 fundamental elements of human development essential to an individual’s acquisition of independence and autonomy, namely:

- Social and emotional development
- Cognitive (intellectual) development
- Linguistic development
- Motor development
- Somatic development

The boxes then placed on the chart are the essential elements of development; once acquired by an individual, they will endure for the rest of their lives. More complex elements are explained and defined in more detail in such a way as to be accessible for all. 

Educational themes are elaborated upon by UmanMap in a more complete way in order to allow adults to deepen their understanding, while the “Historical” tool allows them to create a synthesis of any child or adolescent’s progress in real-time.  

Who is it for?

UmanMap is a working tool for professionals in the health and social care fields, but is equally useful for parents who want to better understand and help their child’s development.

It allows an adult, whether parent, educator, therapist or doctor, to know where a child is within their individual development, to guide them, and do so without losing themselves or the child in the process.

title: Family Health by Wildflower
description:
Keep your family healthier and happier than ever with Family Health. Seamlessly track your baby’s feedings, learn about your husband’s heart health, stay on top of grandma’s screenings and get daily tips about every trimester of your pregnancy, all in one place. The Family Health app’s tools help you to navigate the unique growth of your family, with custom content and features on general health, and specialized info for pregnancy.

• Trackers  |  Vaccination, Growth and Diaper trackers for the little ones. Weight and Height trackers seamlessly sync with your Apple Health app and can be used by the whole family!
• MILESTONES  |  Create profiles for every family member, with health milestones for mom, dad and even grandma. The little ones have detailed milestones for those important first few years.

• WHO TO CALL  |  Simple click-to-call for direct access to your own health team and local health resources. You can even store all of your doctor’s appointments and questions in the Q-List.

Specialized features and health content
• PREGNANCY  |  Track your healthy pregnancy from conception to due date and all the way through postpartum with personalized health info and tools like our Kick Counter and Weight tracker.
• SYMPTOMS & ISSUES  |  Nauseous? Taking prenatal vitamins? First time mom? Scroll through these popular topics -- hand-picked by other expecting women -- with 300+ articles for you and your partner.
• WEEKLY & DAILY  |  From videos and reminders, to tips and tools -- know exactly what is happening each day of your pregnancy.

***  
+ We’re the only app that simplifies the complex health care system by navigating you through the most important and exciting times for your family. Finally, you can connect everything you need in one place: YOUR health insurance, employer benefits, local hospital and neighborhood doctor. 

+ Plus, safety is first when it comes to your family’s health. So we’ve turned to our expert medical writers and physicians. We ensure that all of our content is clinically validated by leading medical organizations like ACOG (American College of Obstetricians & Gynecologists), AAP (American Academy of Pediatrics), AAFP (American Academy of Family Physicians) and NIH (National Institutes of Health. 
***

MEET Wildflower Health
Wildflower Health was born to help women make better healthcare decisions through the device that’s always at hand – their smartphone.
   “When I was pregnant in with my first child I recognized that what should be a time of joy was often tempered by uncertainty about health plan benefits, hospital services and appointment schedules. How could I help myself and my fellow moms better navigate this healthcare system for the entire family? I launched Wildflower Health and the Family Health mobile app to help the Chief Health Officer of the Home track family health with tools to navigate the growth of each family member.” – Leah Sparks, CEO & Founder

---
Family Health by Wildflower is constantly growing too, just like your family. We plan on adding more tools and content for different health topics and conditions in the future, as well as adding more local resources. Have tips? Email us at support@wildflowerhealth.com. title: Gestavida PHR: Pregnancy tracker
description:
Personal Health Record (PHR) for pregnancy. 

Gestavida PHR helps you manage and centralize easily all health information of the mother and baby during pregnancy.

Developed by Carlos Luis Seva Llor. 

Features: 

- Week by week guide with information and tips about pregnancy progress with weekly notifications.
- Customizable charts for tracking variables, both mother and baby: weight, glucose, weight and more.
- Record all health information about mother and baby (diseases, allergies, history, vaccines...).
- Healthcare and tips: birth preparation, pregnancy exercises and videos.
- Agenda and calendar events with notifications: keeps track of appointments with your doctor / midwife or other important events.
- Complete drug database with reminders and notifications.
- Baby names database with more than +3000 names including description and origin.
- Ultrasounds gallery with detail information.
- Box of common daily counters (take fluids, nausea, and more) including kicks and contractions counters.
- Emergency contacts list for to contact in an emergency.

- Share information on social networks (Facebook and Twitter) .

title: Office Yoga - Fitness Workouts
description:
Office Yoga - Fitness at work

Welcome to the world of healthy lifestyle skills at workplace.
Sedentary lifestyle such as sitting on the chair at your workstation for long work hours is very harmful to your body. It reduces blood flow, raises blood sugar and reduces good cholesterol thereby making you very prone to a variety of lifestyle diseases such as heart disease, diabetes, stroke and many more.

Office Yoga app can help you in maintaining good health and preventing lifestyle diseases via a few quick stretching exercises and yoga poses that you can easily perform while at your workplace. This app can be your personal fitness trainer at your workplace.

*** Special Features:
******************

* Supported Languages

العربية, 中国, Nederlands, English, français, Deutsch, Ελληνική, עברית, Indonesia, Italiano, 日本の, 한국어, Polskie, português, русский, Español, Swdeish, ไทย, Український

* YOGA and EXERCISE SCIENCE: Suggested workouts combine the elements and benefits of traditional yoga and modern exercise science.

* ROUTINES FOR DAILY WORKOUT: Daily yoga and exercise program tailored for all age groups. Routine includes yoga poses and exercise suggested by experienced yoga instructors and target full-body workout.

* PRACTICE SESSION: All of the yoga poses and exercises are detailed with HD video, audio and "How to do?" instructions and information on benefits and precautions.

* MY ROUTINE: Design your own daily fitness routine. Also you can add yoga and exercise of your choice to your favorite list.

* BMI and WEIGHT TRACKING: Calculate your Body Mass Index (BMI) and track your weight for weight management.

* Reminder for your daily routine.

*** Key features
*************

* DAILY WORKOUT
  Full-body routine workout to prevent lifestyle diseases and relieve discomforts resulting from sedentary lifestyle.

* STRETCHING EXERCISES
  Stretching exercises and poses to relax your muscles and de-stress you at your workplace.

* STRENGTHENING WORKOUT
  Specific poses to develop strength in your body at your work place without any additional equipment.

* WORKOUT CATEGORIZATION BY BODY AREA
The various exercises and yoga poses are categorized by different areas of the body, so you can easily determine what is best for improving the weak areas of your body.

* BACK EXERCISE
  Simple exercises to prevent back injuries and fatigue caused by prolonged hours of sitting.

* LOWER BODY
  Exercises for strengthening your legs and keep up the muscle tone.

* WRIST & ARM
  Specific Yoga exercises for wrist and arm, specially useful for IT professionals.

* STANDING YOGA
  Yoga workouts that you can perform while standing.

* RELAXATION
  Techniques for staying relaxed at your workspace..

Precautions: Do not over perform any of the poses or exercises and always listen to your body. If you have any physical ailment please consult your doctor or health care professional before attempting any of these suggested exercises.

title: Mama in Shape - Poworkout
description:
Get in shape after pregnancy - regardless the age of the child. Workout easily at home with this app, the workout programs are short and easy to follow. All exercises are shown with videos and text instructions.

STRONGER CORE
With the app, you get exercises that give you stronger core and all over strength for the entire body. You will get better contact with your inner abdominal muscles and learn how to better activate the seat muscles.

FOR THE MOM WHO WANTS TO GET STARTED
The app consists exercises and workout programs for moms - no matter how long since you were pregnant - the workout programs are designed for both moms with new-borns and mothers with older children.

The difference between newly pregnants moms and mothers who just did not get started with the training yet (the child may be a teenager) is the number of times you repeat each exercise program.

The app is also for moms who has get started, maybe a bit sporadic but now it feels like it's time to start properly and from scratch.

HOW TO USE THE APP
Start with workout program 1 and then continue at your own pace. Exercise one or more training programs per time. Exercise each workout program as many times as it feels good, once you get started and taken you through all workout programs, you can then choose the workouts  you feel you need the most and focus on them.

The workouts gradually increase in difficulty, it’s not an even leaning staircase, but the exercises are introduced in the "right" order to get started with the training in a good way.

Use the app regularly, 3-5 times a week for 10-12 weeks and then you will have a stronger mom body.

TRAIN FOR ONLY 5-15 MINUTES
Workouts are quick to done and you can train them separately or combine with power walking or other fitness training if you want to, for example, you can practice one or more workout programs after a spin or dance class.

BY CAROLINE NILSSON
The workouts are designed by the Swedish personal trainer and mother of three Caroline Nilsson, who runs several popular training sites in Sweden and has helped many mothers get in shape. Caroline has developed several training apps together with the business woman and system developer Susanne Jarl.

WORKOUT APPS POWORKOUT
Mom in shape is an app in the series Poworkout (which is a brand that stands for "powerful workouts"), the other training apps are Trim & Tone (body weight training) and Ball & Band (workouts with exercise ball and exercise band).

title: iHypnoBirthPartner
description:
iHypnobirthPartner is the ultimate relaxation aid to enable you to be the best birth companion. IhynobirthPartner has been designed for birth partners and aims to help you prepare both emotionally and mentally for a positive birth partner experience. By listening to the relaxation and positive affirmations regularly during your birth partner's pregnancy, you will practice deep relaxation, and positive visualisations to help you to have enjoyable, calm, controlled, and empowered birth experience. If you learn to condition your mind now it will be much easier to slip into a relaxed state during your partner's labour and birth - and even after your baby is born these techniques will serve you well.

Features:-

Guided relaxation

Birth Partner affirmations

Hints and Tips on how to be the best birth partner you can be

Hints and Tips on getting the most from your audio practice

Male voice on relaxation and affirmations

iHypnobirthPartner was created by Psychologist and hypnatal practitioner Dr Alex McKay, hypnatal & NLP qualified Charlotte Maslen MA HONs. With six children between them they have first hand experience of the power that self-hypnosis and positive affirmations have on pregnancy and birth. They also know how important it was for their birth partners to use this type of relaxation and positive visualisation. This enabled their birth partners to also enjoy the birthing experience. Birth partners are often overlooked and this app aims to help empower them and quip them with the skills required to achieve a confident and relaxed birth partner experience.

title: Advanced Equine Reproductive Ultrasound
description:
Advanced equine reproductive ultrasound is designed for veterinarians already familiar with the examination of the female reproductive tract. It features high quality labeled pictures and videos clearly demonstrating the important structures. All of the pictures and videos are on the phone or iPad and no internet connection is required after the first use.

The App covers;
•Ovarian diseases
•Uterine diseases (endometritis, cysts, pyometra, pneumovagina, uro-uterus)
•Twin diagnosis
•Twin reduction
•Fetal sexing


This App is intended for Veterinary Professionals, including veterinarians and veterinary students.
•Please read the End-User Legal Agreement (EULA) before downloading this application.

The App has been developed by Dr Marco Livini, past coordinator of SIRE (Italian Society of Equine Reproduction) and past President of SIVE (Italian Society of Equine Practitioners).

Comprehensive notes are included for each condition with multiple still images. Fetal sexing is described and carefully illustrated in multiple planes for each stage of gestation. The still pictures demonstrate the classic appearance of each stage and are labeled where necessary. The video loops simulate the real life situation and allow the user to test their observational skills on moving images. This is an invaluable tool for continuing professional education of any veterinarian interested in stud work. 


For more information about this App and upcoming publications, please visit www.veterinaryadvances.com
We have posted a video of the App playing on an iPhone and on an iPad on YouTube.

All of the pictures, videos and text are copyright of Dr Marco Livini and Veterinary Advances Ltd 2013.

description:
Wyoming Medicaid offers pregnant women a great new app. WYhealth Due Date Plus helps you keep track of your pregnancy, set reminders, and get actions personalized just for you. With weekly ultrasound videos and daily advice, WYhealth Due Date Plus can help you get ready for baby.

This app is connected to a free 24/7 Nurse Line, so that you can get help quickly from WYhealth staff. You can also look up free community resources in your area of Wyoming.

There's a lot to learn when you're pregnant! WYhealth Due Date Plus helps you stay on track every step of your pregnancy.

Use this app to track your weight gain, look up symptoms, find out about health issues in pregnancy, keep a list of things to talk about with your doctor, and set reminders so you won’t forget the important things to do when you’re pregnant.

Get weekly updates with ultrasound videos showing what babies look like at each stage of pregnancy. Daily updates give you important tips and inspirational quotes to stay positive and motivated.

Developed in conjunction with a board certified OB who has over 15 years' experience taking care of pregnant women and their babies. Other contributors include nurse midwives and other medical experts.

It’s easy to use – just enter your due date and birth date, and Due Date Plus sets up your pregnancy milestones. When you see something you want to talk to your doctor, midwife or nurse about, you can add it to your Hot List so you can easily remember it at your next appointment.



App Features: 
- Week by week updates 

- Due date calculator 

- Weight gain calculator 
- Wyoming Community Resources Look-Up
- Pregnancy milestones 

- Daily tips and affirmations to stay positive
- Look up symptoms and issues 
- Connect to baby with the Baby Boost relaxation tool
- Expert content for fathers and partners of the mother-to-be

Due Date Plus helps you keep track of all the things an expectant mother needs to do - keep hydrated, take prenatal vitamins, eat well, stay active, and communicate with your doctor or midwife. And of course go to your prenatal appointments!

Due Date Plus can help you understand symptoms or issues that arise throughout your pregnancy, giving you real-time health advice. Your actions can include talking to your health provider about an issue, calling a resource in your area, enrolling in a pregnancy management program, or using one of Due Date Plus' in-app tools to check your weight or take time to relax.

We welcome your comments and suggestions - please email us at team@wildflowerhealth.com.

title: Fertility Astrology
description:
Falling pregnant is something we take for granted – until we struggle with it.

The Fertility Astrology app can tell anyone who wants to know what their ideal fertile times for conception will be in the year ahead – within minutes.

Timing is everything. Astrology and conception are all about cycles and timing.

Many couples struggling with infertility will have to make a decision about when to have treatment, whether or not that treatment is IVF, Artificial Insemination, or a home plan. Time needs to be taken off work and plans need to be shifted.  Very often a large part of the stress involved is who decides when to cycle.  This app hopes to make this decision really easy by giving couples the next three best potentially lucky times in which to try to conceive.  Couples will enter their birth time, date and place into the app, fill out a short medical questionnaire and within minutes the app will give a page of results of the these times, listed in chronological order.  The app will take both charts into consideration and the results will be a combination of the birth data entered. The medical questionnaire will prompt any necessary medical considerations, tests and treatments that might need to take place before conception can be attempted.

Main App Features
•	Caters to different family variations
•	Offers an appropriate medical questionnaire
•	Prompts necessary medical and lifestyle intervention
•	Saves at the exact place in the sequence for quick access on return
•	Computes three potential conception times for the year ahead
•	Suitable for both natural and medically-assisted conception
•	Makes us of Fertility Astrology’s unique astrological calculations.

SOME FREQUENTLY ASKED QUESTIONS - ANSWERED

Who is the “gestational carrier?”
A gestational carrier is the person who intends carrying and giving birth to the baby. So, if you are in a heterosexual relationship, then the female who intends to give birth is the gestational carrier…in a male same sex couple, this person would be the surrogate. If you are a trans couple, whichever one of you is going to be physically carrying the baby and giving birth is the gestational carrier. The partner of the gestational carrier is the person who is in a co-parenting relationship with the carrier, not the sperm donor.

What happens if I don’t know my exact birth time?
The best results are achieved when you enter an accurate birth time. However, a lot of people are not exactly sure of when they are born therefore our suggestion is to enter the time you think were born to the nearest 10-15mins. Some people think they were born between certain time frames - for example 10 and 10.30 - in which case please enter 10.15.  If you have absolutely no idea, then this app is unable to predict reliable times for you. Should you still wish to consult with Nicola please contact her via fertilityastrology.com

What if the atlas does not list the place where I was born?
You will be prompted to enter the nearest available city on the atlas, north or south of the location where you were born.  

Will these results change over time?
No, these results are unlikely to change, unless of course your birth data was incorrect and you now have new information, in which case you will have to re-purchase.

What if I don’t have the information required to fill out the medical questionnaire?
You can always stop and save your information and return later with your test results or additional medical updates. Entering your correct data enables us to optimise the app to give you the most accurate results based on the information you enter.

Please visit www.fertilityastrology.com for more information on our work and on the app and follow us on Facebook.

title: Pregnancy Garbhasanskar
description:
This comprehensive pregnancy care app has been developed by an allopathic Gynaecologist and Pediatrician couple (Dr Vikram Shah & Dr Geetanjali Shah) practising at Dadar, Mumbai, India. Their books and workshops on pregnancy care and garbhasanskar in the last 17 years have been very popular.
This app has been designed for expectant moms and dads to capture the magical aspects of pregnancy in the form of an educational tool.

The highlight of this app is a unique meditation and a mantra (chant) given for every week of pregnancy which makes it a highly sought out empowering tool for Garbhasanskar. Working women who find it difficult to read long texts are delighted with the manageable info and practical tips which they can follow in their busy schedule.

HOW TO USE THE APP COUNTDOWN:

* Countdown widget
* Enter your last menstrual period date(LMP)
* An attractive bar shows your trimester, weeks, days and the time till your delivery

SCROLL INFORMATION WEEKLY OR TOPIC-WISE.

If you want guidelines on the health issues , tap the health tips on any week and then tap the purple arrow on the right hand side down which will allow you to see the health remedies for all weeks

WEEKLY-

YOUR BABY:- Weekly information about your baby's growth and development

YOUR BODY:- Physical changes, symptoms and cravings in your body

GARBHASANSKAR AND HOLISTIC TIPS:- GARBHASANSKAR i.e inculcating virtues in the fetus can be achieved by unique techniques of stimulating the intelligence of the unborn child. This app gives you different weekly meditations to nurture the expectant mom's mind in the 'holistic tips' section. As a part of garbhasanskar , it teaches the methods of stimulating the 5 senses of the baby , 'Garbha- samvaad' or communicating with the foetus and 'Garbhasangeet' for musical auditory enhancement of baby's brain. Different spiritual affirmations help to imbibe noble qualities in the baby which the parents are taught through 'Garbha-chintan' charts.

WEEKLY HEALTH TIPS:- Remedies for common complaints like backache, indigestion, headaches, muscle cramps, urinary frequency etc are given according to the week of pregnancy. A combination of scientific and traditional remedies is used for soon to be moms. The fact that a doctor couple practising allopathy and involved in childbirth are advising these remedies, makes them very practical and safe.

WEEKLY MANTRAS:- Powerful priceless mantras or chants specific for that week are given.The expectant mom has to recite these mantras aloud daily for that particular week. This probably is the only app where western medicine tips and spiritual mantras are so beautifully blended together.

LABOUR AND CHILDBIRTH:- From week 32 onwards amazing ‘smooth labour techniques’ with labour breathing , postures, accupressure, diet, and labour affirmations are given.The spouse or labour partner also should read these techniques.

SHOP:- Online purchases are available for the following
* Garbhasanskar and pregnancy care books in English , Hindi & Marathi
* Mantras and Garbhasangeet CD's
* Flashcards, Mathscards, Multi-language Cards to be read aloud by expectant moms & flashed to the newborn after birth.
* Pregnancy pillow for exercise and sleeping and breastfeeding pillows
* Ready reckoner charts-- labour chart, exercise charts, garbhasanskar chart, diet chart, educative toys chart, shishusankar charts.
* Crawling track on rent

WORKSHOPS:- This app gives infomation about the following courses
* Antenatal classes in the icon ' Pregnancy '
* Childbrain stimulation class( newborn to 5yrs) in the icon 'Child'
* Preconception classes in the icon 'Plan a baby'
* SPA
* ‘Healing moms’ spa is for pregnant and postnatal moms and those planning a baby
* Detoxification and relaxation techniques with music, massage, and meditation in the safe ambience of a maternity hospital are given.

title: ovolane
description:

Natural - Smart - Comfortable - Safe ...

The slim, tampon size, intelligent ovolane® sensor records your temperature progression precisely - while you sleep.

After it’s removal, the ovolane® sensor utilizes Bluetooth to automatically send the temperature data to the ovolane® app.

From the temperature data, the ovolane® app determines your fertile days, the time of your ovulation and clearly presents both in a calendar, as a monthly graph and a cycle calendar (see screenshots). You can also record brief notes and other activities and symptoms for each day.

In addition, based on your past cycles, the ovolane® App prognoses your future cycle, can detect the absence of an ovulation and much more …

title: Birth Positions - an active choice
description:
Birth is movement

Birth Positions - an active choice is you and your partners guide to an active birth.
The app is developed by experienced midwives, and it will help you to use your body optimally during labour and birth.
The app contains video of how many different labour- and birth positions you can choose at home and in the delivery room.
Each video is available in two versions: One for you, and one for your partner.

Why is it important to know about birth positions?
Movement, change of positions and resting will affect both the perception of pain, and the duration of labour.
You should be aware of the possibillities, and know what advantages and disadvantages there is to the different positions.
Use the app for your birth preparation, and discuss birth positions with your partner and your birth professionals.

Labour positions are used in the first phase of birth.
At this time, it is important that you relax and rest well in between contractions, in order to save your strength for later.
Movement and relaxation will help your body to make room for the baby, and can relieve pain.

Birth positions are used in the active phase.
When pushing, you need positions where you can work actively with your contractions.
Movement will help your pelvis to widen, so your baby can move through the birth canal.

Both labour and birth positions can affect the intensity and effect of your labour.
Different positions will make for more or less contact with your partner or midwife, and your possibilities of moving, resting and relaxing.
We’ll guide you through the different positions, and tell your partner what he can do to support you.

Birth is movement, and birth is hard labour.
While pregnant, you can prepare for birth through exercise.
It is also important to remember to eat and drink during labour, both for you, and for your partner who’ll be supporting you physically and mentally, and will tend to forget himself.

Functions:
-  Video demonstrations of labour positions
-  Video demonstrations of birth positions
-  My downloads: Your downloaded files, which are now available for viewing off-line

Developed by experienced clinicians
The app is developed by midwife PhD Sara Kindberg from GynZone, in collaboration with midwife MMid Marie Louise Mastrup Knudsen, midwife and clinical expert Li Thies Lagergren, midwife and anthropologist Peggy Seehafer, and Midwife and clinical expert Rita Lønne.

title: Fetal Weight Calculator - Estimate Weight and Growth Percentile
description:
The Fetal Weight Calculator helps physicians, nurses, midwives, medical residents, students and other medical professionals quickly compute prenatal weight estimates by using one or more key measurements from a fetal sonogram (ultrasound). Weight estimates can provide helpful guidance during a mother's pregnancy and can also be used to help diagnose other potential issues.

Users provide the abdominal circumference (AC) as well as one or more of the following: biparietal diameter (BPD), femur length (FL) and head circumference (HC). The app then uses one of the standard fetal weight estimation algorithms (Shepard or Hadlock) to provide the estimate.

If the estimated fetal age is available, the app can also provide a growth percentile based on either the Hadlock growth curve or the World Health Organization growth curve.

title: GraviLog سجل الحمل

"سجل الحمل" ( عربي/ English) هو نتاج عمل اكثر من سنتين لجهد مشترك من اطباء وخبراء في الوطن العربي وفي جامعة هارفرد الامريكية، وهو دليل المراه الحامل.

انت والحمل: كيف تجعلي شهور حملك اجمل 9 أشهر؟ ما عليك الا انت تتعرفي على احدث الطرق العلمية في تجنب اعراض الحمل الغير المرغوبة مثل كيف تتخلصي من حرقة المعدة، الم الظهر والساقين، الدوالي، الغثيان الصباحي، الصداع والم الراس وغيرها الكثير!
سجل الحمل، تطبيق ذكي يمكن طبيبك من مراقبة صحتك وصحة جنينك وانت في البيت!، تواصلي مع طبيبك من خلال ربط التطبيق بنظام سجل الحمل GraviLog  الخاص بالاطباء من خلال الموقع الالكتروني www.GraviLog.com.
الان ولاول مرة احصلي على سجلك الطبي الالكتروني مجانا، حيث يؤرشف جميع زيارات ومشاهدات الطبيب ويكون مرجعا طبيا لك. بامكانك الحصول على نتائج فحوصاتك المخبرية والطبية والالترا ساوند من خلال هاتفك المحمول.
يقوم تطبيق سجل الحمل بتذكيرك اليا بموعد اجراء الفحوصات الدورية وزيارة الطبيب وتناول الدواء. كما ويمكنك التطبيق من البحث عن طبيب تخصص نسائية وتوليد حسب الدولة والمدينة المطلوبة والاتصال بهم مباشرة من التطبيق.
حملي التطبيق مجانا وانضمي لشبكة مواقع التواصل الاجتماعي سجل الحمل GraviLog.

مع سجل الحمل.. حملك سهل!
\f
The first healthcare and medical app for pregnant women based on World Health Organization (WHO) standards and reviewed by the Ministry of Health.
GraviLog is the product of a compound and intensive work for more than two years of joint efforts of doctors and experts from Harvard University and the Arab world. What to expect when you are expecting, is found in this app, hello my baby, I’m expecting! 
GraviLog app starts from pregnancy planning stage, day by day and week by week with healthcare and medical information, here you will find your baby center; fetus development during the 40 weeks of pregnancy with 40 3D image of the fetus. Full nutrition guide and medication guide during pregnancy. All about your pregnancy tracker and baby tracker, what you are looking for is just a full guide for pregnancy and baby during your pregnancy weeks.
Pregnancy Calculator provides an accurate calculation of gestational age and expected delivery up to 99% accuracy. Turn your pregnancy month to the most beautiful months by learning how to avoid the undesired pregnancy symptoms like heartburn, back pain, legs pain, varicose veins, morning sickness, headaches and many more!
GraviLog enables your doctor to monitor your health and your fetus health even while you are at home and provides a communication channels with your doctor through GraviLog online system for obstetricians and gynecologists (www.GraviLog.com).  
For the first time, now, you can get your Free Electronic Medical Record when connecting with your doctor. Moreover, you can get the results of your laboratory and medical test, including the ultrasound right away from your smartphone. 
GraviLog is a smart app, that, and based on your pregnancy week, it reminds you with your periodic due tests, doctor’s visit, medication intake and others.
Search for a doctor in your area and make a call directly from the app. 
GraviLog, is all you need during your pregnancy.

title: NannyNotes Baby Tracker Sheet
description:
NannyNotes Baby Tracker and Daily Sheet allows for parents, nannies, and caregivers to easily communicate. It is the replacement for the daily sheet with the ability to add notes, photos, videos, memos and so much more!

NannyNotes is the daily sheet replacement that keeps parents informed about their children while away at work or traveling. With an intuitive and easy to use baby tracker, caregivers can quickly log sleep schedules, diapers, feedings and activities with notes, photos and videos that are immediately available for parents. Don’t miss out on your child’s day while you are away. Use NannyNotes and stay connected no matter where you are!

"As a first time mom it was hard going back to work after having our son. With NannyNotes I am able to constantly check during the day and see what my little man is doing" - Amy

What does a day with NannyNotes look like?
Parents can start the day by adding a memo or two for the caregiver. A memo notification will appear and contain a reminder such as laundry or going to a swim lesson. Parents can also add a note just like a caregiver about when the child wakes up, their diaper and and what they ate for breakfast. This information will all be available for the caregiver when they start their day. 

Child wakes up early? Now the caregiver is aware and perhaps the nap might be a bit early that day. 

Throughout the day the caregiver logs notes such as sleep schedules, snacks, diapers and activities. Throughout the day parents can see the activity in real time on their device. When the parent comes home this information is all accessible to them. 

Did the child skip their nap?- Perhaps bed time should be earlier? Was lunch later than normal? Perhaps dinner should be later that night.

NannyNotes is the app that will keep everyone connected and in sync with their child’s day!

"I often travel for work which can put me in different timezones. NannyNotes allows me to see what my daughter is doing with our Nanny at any time." - Nate

Features
* Track feedings, sleep schedules, diapers, bottles, and activities with notes, photos and videos.
* Receive a daily email with all the notes and photos entered for that day.
* Add unlimited children, caregivers, nannies and family members.
* Intuitive interface makes adding notes quick and simple.
* Updates appear instantly on your device as connections log activity.
* Push notifications are sent when notes and memos are added.
* Caregivers can use the app and share days with parents by text message if they do not have the app!
* Parents can add memos and reminders for caregivers. Need to make sure laundry gets done or add a reminder about swim lessons.? Add a memo!
* Unlimited storage. Add as many photos and notes as you wish. Everything is saved to the cloud and synced across all devices.
* Keep an unlimited history of all your child’s notes and photos grouped by day.
* Any photo that is entered into NannyNotes can be saved to your phone for sharing on any social network.
* Support, we are here to help! Have a question or a great idea? Let us know and we will respond as soon as possible. NannyNotes is an app built by parents for parents.
* Security. Take comfort in knowing that everything is stored safely and securely.


Visit: http://www.nannynotes.net for more information.

description:

WellMama provides easy 5 and 15 minute sequences of Yoga poses proven to help mothers in the postpartum phase to relieve pain and discomfort, strengthen their back, pelvic floor and core muscles, cope with post-pregnancy stress and revitalise their body and mind.

• Revitalise and strengthen your back muscles to prevent back pain
• Relax and calm your mind with restorative yoga poses at home
• Regain the balance of mind & body with yoga sequences to release stress after baby
• Energise and boost your mood

WellMama app offers 2 types of sequences for mothers to pick from: 
• 5 minute sequences of yoga exercises that don’t require props or equipment. 
• 15 minute sequences of yoga poses using props. Common items from around the house can be used to substitute yoga props.

IMPORTANT: consult your physician first before beginning a new nutrition, yoga or fitness regimen, especially if you’ve just had a baby and/or experience postpartum body issues.
TOP FEATURES 

• TAILORED TO YOUR MOOD: Select the sequence most suited to your wellbeing at that moment: 5 minute without equipment or 15 minute with props making it easy to fit into a busy mothers daily routine
• TAILORED TO YOUR MIND & BODY: Yoga sequences for 3 areas; Mind & Spirit (restorative and energising), Neck & Shoulders (addressing neck pain and shoulder pain) and Lower Back (ease the back pain and pelvic zone issues). 
• TRACKS: Progress tracker automatically saves your success to help you visualise and track your training, by week and month. Achieve rewards for taking care of yourself and revitalising your wellbeing.
• REWARDS: Receive reward posters at the end of all yoga sequences to give you motivation and support to continue to help getting rid of pain and strengthening your attitude.
• EXPERT: Yoga sequences are developed by yoga experts specifically for post-pregnancy body problems – to help you deal with and relieve sore back, neck and shoulders, stress and tiredness 
• NO SPECIAL EQUIPMENT NEEDED: just everyday items to perform yoga poses safely and correctly which you can do in the comfort of your own home.
• GUIDES: Beautifully designed step-by-step Visual and Audio instructions to ensure you’re doing each pose correctly. Includes a ‘Right and Wrong Way’ section to better understand the actions in the poses and avoid common mistakes especially useful for postpartum stage after having a baby.

Our WellMama exercises not only help relieve aches & pains & reduce stress but also prevent pain coming back to you whilst building physical and mental strength, energising the body and calming the mind. 

Get WellMama PRO for pain-free and Happy mothering!

Disclaimer: you should consult your physician before beginning a new yoga/fitness regime. You should not rely on any information available through the app as a substitute for professional medical advice, diagnosis or treatment.

title: Moment Health
description:
The Moment Health app is here to change the lives of parents around the globe and bring maternal mental health into the mainstream.

Our app has been developed alongside leading clinicians and healthcare professionals to ensure it’s a top service for new parents like you. 

We’re incredibly excited to be on this parenting journey with you. Together, we can normalise Maternal Mental Health and #MakeItMainstream.

Here’s what the app can do for you, and a quick how-to-use-it guide. 

What The Moment App Does:
The Moment Health app is for new and expectant mums and their families. 

Our app is committed to making maternal mental health mainstream. Research shows that through early intervention, parents suffering perinatal depression and associated anxieties have an 80-90 per cent chance of recovery.

That’s exactly why we’re harnessing the positive power of technology with an app that screens for prenatal and postnatal depression and associated anxieties, through the following innovative features:

CHECKER 
Our early intervention symptoms checker can be used to detect signs of prenatal and postnatal depression and associated anxieties.

It’s an easy-to-use, evidence-based series of quick questions, used by GPs, clinicians and other healthcare providers the world over to screen for early signs of  prenatal and postnatal depression and associated anxieties.

TRACKER 
The tracker allows you to quickly record your emotions and moods from pregnancy right through to early parenthood. 

It provides a Weekly Mood Report, which shows at a glance how you’ve been feeling over the last days, weeks and months. 

With the Tracker, any emotional changes that could potentially lead to a negative impact on your wellbeing can be picked up and treated very early on. 

COMMUNITY 
The Moment Health community is made up of likeminded parents like you. 

The four major focuses for the community are to provide (1) Connectedness, (2) Support, (3) Companionship, and (4) Advice for our members.

Our community provides a space for our members to share openly and react with empathy in a safe and supportive environment.

LOCATOR 
Through our location tool, mums and dads can find exactly the kind of support and resources they need that are close and convenient to them. 

The location tool recommends centres and groups in close proximity to you, based on where you are and what kind of support you need.

That's why this App lets you hear a small beep at 60- and 90- seconds! When you press stop it automatically saves the start/stop time and calculates the two most important things: the duration of the contraction and the time that has passed since the last contraction!

In the 2nd tab you will find a nice summary of all timed contractions where you can instantly see if you can call your midwife already. You can even e-mail this overview to your midwife or perhaps after giving birth to yourself if you'd like!

The 3rd tab provides more information about giving birth and the different phases of contractions.

Download this App and timing contractions will be so easy that you've got enough time left to relax!

title: ESHRE (Journals)
description:
About the app
The ESHRE (European Society of Human Reproduction and Embryology) Journals app from Oxford University Press enables you to read the leading journals Human Reproduction, Human Reproduction Update, Molecular Human Reproduction, and Human Reproduction Open, both online and offline on your iOS device (provided you have a relevant personal subscription, institutional subscription, or society membership).
You can:
• download issues when you’re online, so that you can read them whether you’re connected to the Internet or not
• view the tables of contents for issues when you’re online, whether you have downloaded them yet or not 
• easily read issues from cover to cover by swiping through articles
• download and read advance articles (published ahead of print)
• download and read the PDF version of an article
• use the in-app search feature
• bookmark your favourite articles
• add your own notes to articles
• share articles by email or on social media

About the journals
Human Reproduction features full-length, peer-reviewed papers reporting original research, concise clinical case reports, and opinions and debates on topical issues. Papers published cover the clinical science and medical aspects of reproductive physiology, pathology, and endocrinology, including andrology, gonad function, gametogenesis, fertilization, embryo development, implantation, early pregnancy, genetics, genetic diagnosis, oncology, infectious disease, surgery, contraception, infertility treatment, psychology, ethics, and social issues.
Human Reproduction Update publishes comprehensive and systematic review articles in human reproductive physiology and medicine. Basic, transitional, and clinical topics related to reproduction are of primary interest. This includes all the relevant areas of andrology, embryology, infertility, gynaecology, pregnancy, reproductive endocrinology, reproductive epidemiology, reproductive genetics, reproductive immunology, and reproductive oncology.
Molecular Human Reproduction publishes articles on the basic science of human reproductive physiology and pathology, endocrinology, andrology, gonadal function, gametogenesis, fertilization, embryo development, implantation, pregnancy, and contraception.
Human Reproduction Open is a new, fully open-access journal in reproductive medicine. It seeks to improve the understanding of reproductive medicine, and improve the quality of clinical care, by making scientific research freely accessible to those providing or seeking treatment. 
The journals are published on behalf of the European Society of Human Reproduction and Embryology (ESHRE) by Oxford University Press.
Oxford University Press is a department of the University of Oxford. It furthers the University’s objective of excellence in research, scholarship, and education by publishing worldwide.

title: ObstetriCalc
description:
ObstetriCalc is designed to provide a set of pregnancy key dates. It is the only obstetrical wheel that allows for defining your own date or date range (e.g., LMP+3Weeks+2days, or Conception + 20weeks). A special interface dedicated to an easy definition of dates allows for daily and intensive use. The key data to be defined or calculated are:
•The last menstrual period,
•The conception date,
•The due date,
•The embryo length at a given date,
•The gestational age at a given date.
The embryo length or the gestational age could therefore be defined by using previous ultrasound measure. 

At any time a set of consistent data (dates, gestational age or embryo length) is proposed, the reference data being outlined with a blue star.

A large calendar allows for a global view of all user-defined dates.

ObstetriCalc is highly adaptable through the definition of additional dates (or date range) that are defined by adding days or weeks to one of the previous reference date (LMP, due date, conception date).
